Argentina , Uruguay Sign Pact on River Dredging
BUENOS AIRES , November 18 ( Xinhua ) -- Argentina and Uruguay signed a joint statement on Wednesday concerning the dredging of the Uruguay River bordering the two countries .
The dredging , estimated to cost about 100 million U.S. dollars , will open the river to boost the trade between member states of the South American Common Market ( Mercosur ) , a regional block that also includes Brazil and Paraguay .
The pact was signed by visiting Uruguayan President Julio Maria Sanguinetti and his Argentine counterpart Carlos Menem during a meeting on Argentina 's Martin Garcia island .
